article_title: Kiosk Company Wants To Bring The Doctor's Office To Workplaces, Pharmacies And Impoverished Villages

article_metadata.description: “What I found was that basically an urgent care is about like running a hair salon,” Steve Cashman says. “You rent a building, and you get some staff in there, and there isn’t real ingenuity to it, there isn’t any real efficiency to it.”
article_metadata.author: Dan Alexander
